Honeymoon Dump 1/3.

Shinjuku Station to hotel - a much farther walk than anticipated. Seoul from Lotte World Tower. Stairway postings en route to a familiar camera store. Rach and Hachiko finally meet 🥰. Kyoto backstreets. People watching in the rain. Exiting Myeong-dong station. Jagalchi. Entering Kyoto station. The beautiful, freezing, first morning in Seoul.

Honeymoon in transit. 

Seoul via Lotte Tower observation deck. Myeong-dong station. Shinkansen seating (Rachel finding out that the bullet train in the movie was a futuristic rendition). Cabin views between Kyoto and Osaka. Fugu Omakase entrance with just enough poison to tickle the lips. Rimowa obsession. Tokyo from New York Bar. 2nd gen Elantra outside Seomyeon station. Countryside fire on the train to Busan and a few extra blue details to wrap up the dump.

Tokyo. Hakone. Kyoto. Osaka. Seoul. Busan. Honeymoon wrap.

Panda spotting in Kyoto. Rimowa in Hakone. HeyRach giving her best hearts to Kyoto. KTX views. Busan from Lotte Hotel. Dinner with friends from Vietnam. Osaka International. Seoul from viewport. More Jagalchi. Palo Museum trail Hakone. 

Thanks @hey_rach for sticking it with me through all the activities ❤️.

Once upon a time...

Directed by yours truly.
